question.title: String compareTo() in java
question.body:
Consider:

String s1 = "ABc";
String s2 = "abc";
System.out.println(s1.compareTo(s2));

On which basis the output will be -32 if only the first character decimal value of s1 and s2 are compared? Is this the correct way?

If String contains more than 1 character, then we should compare each character, but compareTo() method only compares the first character. Isnâ€™t this a bug?
